/*
 * $Id: ChangeLog,v 1.575 2003/01/02 09:05:14 ronpinkas Exp $
 */

/* Use this format for the entry headers:
   YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM UTC[-|+]hhmm Your Full Name <your_email@address>
   For example:
   2002-12-01 23:12 UTC+0100 Foo Bar <foo.bar@foobar.org>
*/

2003-01-02 12:11 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * include/hbtrace.h
  * source/rtl/trace.c
    + Added hb_traceInit() and hb_traceExit()

  * source/vm/cmdarg.c
    + Added support for new hb_traceInit()
    + Added support for //NOTRACE application swtitch to disable auto creation of trace.log file.

  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added support for new hb_traceExit()

2003-01-02 01:03 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    ! Fixed HB_P_FUNCTION, HB_P_FUNCTION, HB_P_SEND, and HB_P_SENDSHORT to be Thread Safe.

2003-01-02 07:28 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * include/inet.h
    ! Using winsock2 instead of winsock. Originarily, it was that way, but
      somehow this has been changed.

2003-01-02 07:01 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/rtl/inet.c
    * removed warning when not compiling with thread support

  * include/inet.h
    ! Fixed compilation ( unresolved SD_BOTH ) on some BCC installations.

2003-01-02 05:44 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/thread.c
    + Now StartThread on method can be called both with a method pointer or
      with a method name:
        StartThread( oMyObject, oMyMethodPtr, ... )
      or
        StartThread( oMyObject, "MethodName", ... )

  * tests/mttest.prg
    * Changed one of the StartThraed to show the "methodname" call.


2003-01-02 04:20 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * include/hbstack.h
    * Default compilation is now WITHOUT threads; -DHB_THREAD_SUPPORT
      must be specified for thread functions to be included.

  * include/thread.h
  * source/vm/thread.c
    * Changed grammar of StartThread Function as follow (all are
      alternatives)
        StarThread( @Function(), param1 ... paramN )
        StarThread( "Function_Name", param1 ... paramN )
        StarThread( {codeblock}, param1 ... paramN )
        StarThread( Object, Method, param1 ... paramN )
      This allows to pass an object to a function when starting a
      thread as a normal parameter.

  * tests/client.prg
  * tests/mtcomplex.prg
  * tests/mtgc.prg
  * tests/mttest.prg
    * Modified to reflect the change in StartThread grammar.

2003-01-01 21:51 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/garbage.c
    + Added InetCRLF() function in inet module, just a shortcut nice to have.

2003-01-01 19:10 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/garbage.c
    ! Now lock on hb_gcGripGet/Drop are working again.

2002-12-31 16:50 UTC-0300 Luiz Rafael Culik <culikr@uol.com.br>
  * source/vm/thread.c
    ! On Conectiva Linux More then 1 line inside #if/#elif/#endif must be inside {}

2002-12-31 13:10 UTC-0300 Luiz Rafael Culik <culikr@uol.com.br>
  * source/vm/thread.c
    ! Fixed include of time.h and sys/time.h on linux

2002-12-31 13:00 UTC-0300 Luiz Rafael Culik <culikr@uol.com.br>
  * source/vm/fm.c
    ! Fixed Compilation Error on Line 751 and 945(usage of HB_THREAD_SUPPORT with
    out the HB_FM_STATISTICS defined (Reported by Itamar Lins)

2002-12-31 08:05 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>

  * include/thread.h
    * Default HB_CRITICAL_LOCK for nonwindows systems has become Light
      Weight Reentrant Mutex
    * LWR lockinig Implemented as a macro
      (you should make clean after update)

  * source/rtl/console.c
    * Using HB_CRITICAL_LOCK for locking console, as it is now defined
      to be always reentrant.

  * source/vm/garbage.c
    * Using HB_CRITICAL_LOCK to lock GC, as it is now defined to be always
      reentrant.
    % Under linux, do not lock hb_gcGripGet/hb_gcGripDrop. This is a temporary
      hack:is working but we must find out why this lock causes deadlocks
      AND possibly sigsev, while removing it deadlock is gone and seg faults
      are far less. Under windows this to be working, so I left that alone.

  * source/vm/thread.c
    ! Now mutex at PRG level are working again: CreateMutex() LockMutex() etc
      are working again now.
    + Now StopThread() can be given an optional second parameter that is a
      mutex on which the target thread might be subscribing, so to release
      it more cleanly. Just a finesse, but is nice to have it.

  * tests/mtcomplex.prg
    * The second StopThread() has been updated to use the new grammar.

2002-12-30 16:56 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * source/vm/arrayshb.c
    ! Fixed Array() to be Thread Safe.

  * source/vm/hvm.c
  * source/vm/arrays.c
  * source/vm/codebloc.c
  * source/vm/thread.c
  * source/vm/garbage.c
    ! Many fixes to be Thread Safe.

