2002-12-29 00:28 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * include/thread.h
  * include/hbapi.h
  * source/vm/thread.c
    + Added hb_threadIsLocalRef( void )

  * include/hbstack.h
    + Added #define STACK_THREADHB_ITEMS 100

  * source/rtl/console.c
  * source/rtl/errorapi.c
  * source/rtl/idle.c
  * source/rtl/inet.c
  * source/vm/arrays.c
  * source/vm/estack.c
  * source/vm/fm.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
  * source/vm/itemapi.c
    * Corrected naming convention for new thread functions.

  * source/vm/garbage.c
    * Added optional logical paramater lForceCollection to HB_GCALL() to force collection even if GC statistcs do not justify collection.
    ! GC is now Thread Safe and much optimized. xHarbour applications should be significantly faster.

2002-12-28 09:05 UTC-0300 Horacio Roldan <harbour_ar@yahoo.com.ar>
   * source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
   * source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx2.h
        ! fixed bug (search path related),
          reported by Jacek Potempa <Jacek.Potempa@otc.pl>
        ! fixed GPF bug reported by Alex Schaft <alexs@quicksoftware.co.za>
        + added support for DBOI_KEYCOUNTRAW, DBOI_KEYNORAW == DBOI_RECNO,
          DBOI_KEYTYPE, DBOI_KEYSIZE, DBOI_FULLPATH
        ! fixed: DBOI_BAGNAME
        ! fix return value when there's no active order to: DBOI_FILEHANDLE,
          DBOI_ISCOND, DBOI_ISDESC, DBOI_UNIQUE, DBOI_POSITION, DBOI_RECNO,
          DBOI_KEYNORAW, DBOI_KEYCOUNT, DBOI_KEYCOUNTRAW.
          This makes ordKeyNo() = recno() and ordKeyCount() = lastrec()
          in such case. Reported by Hernán Diego Ceccarelli
          <hceccarelli@cesotech.com.ar>
        + added helper function hb_cdxOrdListClear
        ! structural index isn't closed anymore
        ! fixed ordKeyNo() and ordKeyCount() to respect filters, they also
          respect the set deleted but only when there is a filter (as C53)
        ! fixed ordScope(0/1, ""), reported by Jean-Christophe AVARGUES and
          Blue Face

   * source/rdd/workarea.c
        ! fix to fieldname, reported by Luiz Rafael Culik

   * include/ord.ch
   * include/dbstruct.ch
        ! minor changes
   * source/rdd/dbcmd.c
        ! fixed GPF, reported by Patrick Mast

2002-12-27 21:41 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * include/hbapi.h
    * Excluded estack.h from being included when building compiler.
      This fixes many compiles error related to premature inclusion of windows.h on Windows platforms.

  * source/rtl/console.c
  * source/vm/fm.c
  * source/vm/garbage.c
    * Added guard to NOT call hb_LWRM_[un]lock() unless MT is indded utilized.
      This fixes GPF related to th eabove functions in NON MT applications.

2002-12-27 23:28 UTC+0100    Giancarlo Niccolai <giancarlo@niccolai.ws>
  * include/hbstack.h
  * include/inet.h
  * source/rtl/inet.c
  * source/vm/estack.c
  * source/vm/thread.c
    ! compilation problems with -DHB_NO_DEFAULT_THREADS are now fixed

  * source/rtl/inet.c
    * Removed completely (using comments) locking mechanism upon sockets. To be studied
      more deeply when MT/GC is working.

2002-12-26 03:38 UTC+0100  Giancarlo Niccolai <giancarlo@niccolai.ws>
  * include/thread.h
    source/vm/thread.c
    + Added multiplatform lightweight reentrant mutex to be used internally by x-harbour
    + hb_LWRM_lock( HB_LWR_MUTEX *lpMutex ) / hb_LWRM_unlock( HB_LWR_MUTEX *lpMutex )

  * source/rtl/console.c
    * Changed the internal mutex to a lightweight reentrant mutex

  * source/rtl/idle.c
     % Added a "marker" around the point that generates an error in MT. Will have to work it
     out in the next days

  * source/rtl/inet.c
    * Commented out mutex sections; will have to decide if keep them (and turn them into LWRM or
      remove them) in the next few days

  * source/vm/fm.c
    source/vm/garbage.c
    ! Added mutex around concurrent allocation/deallocation of shared memory.

