2002-12-18 05:40 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  + include/thread.h
  + source/vm/thread.c
    + New MT support originated by Giancarlo Niccolai [gian@niccolai.ws]
      Revisions and additions by Ron Pinkas

  * include/hbcomp.h
    - Removed unneeded #include.

  * include/hbstack.h
    + Added support for new MT

  * source/vm/estack.c
    + Added #ifdef guarded hb_getCurrentStack() as an alternative to dirrect access to hb_stack.

  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added: #ifdef guarded hb_contextInit() to hb_vmInit()
    + Added: #ifdef guarded Sleep Loop to to hb_vmQuit()

  * source/pp/pptable.c
    * Changed definitions of @ x,y SAY ... to pass Row & Col as additional paramaters to DevOut*()
      /* This is required so that more efficent Mutex can be set for the combined operation. */

  * source/rtl/console.c
    + Added MT Mutex support to all PRG level Output Functions.
    * Added 2 optional paramaters nRow, nCol to DevOut().

  * source/rtl/devoutp.prg
    * Added 2 optional paramaters nRow, nCol to DevOutPict().

  * source/rtl/tprint.c
  * source/rtl/tprinter.c
    * Minor corrections.

  * makefile.bc
    + Added support for thread.c

  + tests/mttest.prg
    + New test file to demonstrate new MT capability.

  * source/vm/arrays.c
    * Corrected comment.

  * source/rtl/errorsys.prg
    + Added TraceLog() just before Alert()

  * source/rtl/regex.c
    * Work in progress.

2002-12-17 12:40 UTC-0300 Walter Negro <anegro@overnet.com.ar>
  * source/tget.prg
    ! Fix, UpdateBuffer() should not actualize the variable if the value
      was not modified.

    Reported by Francisco Gamboa and Horacio Roldan

2002-12-16 20:20 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * include/hbapi.h
  * source/vm/classes.c
    * Added 4th optional paramater BOOL *bConstructor to hb_objGetMthd().

  * source/vm/hvm.c
    ! Fixed hb_vmSend() to always return Self if method is a Constructor.

    /*
       This was NOT Clipper OOP engines compatible, as I recently found to my surprise that
       RETURN NIL was ending some METHOD New(...) and it was working perfectly in Clipper [Objects].
       Same code was naturally breaking in xHarbour. Now I don't consider RETURN of anything other
       than Self as good practice, but for compatibility, I thought this should be fixed.
     */

2002-12-16 08:31 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
   * include/hbapi.h
     * Added () around macro paramaters expansion.

2002-12-15 22:00 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
