  * include/hbapi.h
  * include/hbapiitm.h
  * include/hbvmpub.h
  * tests/pp_harb.ch
    < Reverted last change related to bNeedLock, hb_itemUnRef() and exclusion of statics from GC.

  * include/hbpcode.h
  * source/compiler/genc.c
  * source/compiler/hbfix.c
  * source/compiler/hbpcode.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    - Removed support for HB_P_PUSHGLOBALREF

  * source/compiler/harbour.c
    + Added Error on attempting to pass a GLOBAL by refrence.

  * source/pp/ppcore.c
    ! Fixed bug with support of X in #[X]command and #[X]translate if abbreviation used.
    - Removed support for #unxcommand and #unxtranslate.
    * Finalized implementation of [x]uncommand and [x]untranslate.
      /*
          NOTE: #uncommand and #untranslate do NOT require MATCH specification [nor RESULT specification] the KEY itself is sufficient.
               #Xuncommand and #Xuntranslate DO require correct MATCH specification, but do NOT require RESULT specification.

          IOW:
               1. #uncommand will search a matching most recent #[x]command based on the KEY only, and will remove it if found.
               2. #untranslate will search a matching most recent #[x]translate based on the KEY only, and will remove it if found.
               3. #Xuncommand will search a matching most recent #[x]command based on the KEY, AND Match Rule, and will remove it if found.
               4. #Xuntranslate will search a matching most recent #[x]translate based on the KEY, AND MatchRule, and will remove it if found.

       */

  * tests/global1.prg
    - Removed sample of Global passed by refernce.

2002-09-20 23:40 UTC -0300 Luiz Rafael Culik <culikr@uol.com.br>
  * utils/hbmake/hbmake.prg
    * Minor changes.
        - The select Main file, only allow to select between all files need by the app
        - The select main file is now sorted

2002-09-20 12:44 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * include/hbapi.h
    * Changed hb_vmGlobalLock() to a macro HB_ITEM_LOCK()
    * Changed hb_vmGlobalUnlock() to a macro HB_ITEM_UNLOCK()

  * include/hbvmpub.h
    + Added member bNeedLock to hb_struRefer

  * include/hbapiitm.h
  * source/vm/itemapi.c
    * Changed hb_itemUnRef() to accept 2nd paramater pointer to BOOL.

  * source/vm/arrays.c
  * source/vm/classes.c
  * source/vm/codebloc.c
  * source/vm/extend.c
  * source/vm/garbage.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
  * source/vm/memvars.c
  * tests/pp_harb.ch
    * Changed all hb_itemUnRef() calls to pass 2nd paramater pointer to BOOL, or NULL.

  * source/vm/memvars.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added logic to HB_ITEM_UNLOCK given STATIC and GLOBAL just before assignment, and HB_ITEM_LOCK just after assignment.
    + Added logic to HB_ITEM_UNLOCK given VAR just before assignment, and HB_ITEM_LOCK just after assignment -
      if VAR the De-Refernce VAR is a GLOBAL or STATIC.

  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added logic to mark a variables pushed by refernce asRefer.bNeedLock as TRUE for GLOBALs and STATICs and FALSE for LOCALs
      /* MEMVARs don't use asRefer. */
    + Added LOCK to s_aStatics.
    + Added UNLOCK to all s_aStatics elements in hb_vmQuit().

  * source/vm/garbage.c
    - Removed hb_vmIsStaticRef() from sweep scan, since STATIC should no longer require garbage collection.

  /*
     NOTE: Garbage collection should be much faster, and thus applications which have frequent calls to HB_GCALL()
           (like FWH) should be noticably faster after this change. I tested heavily, but will appreciate extensive
           testing, [and reports] from everyone.
   */

