2002-09-15 22:31 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * include/hbcomp.h
  * include/hbpcode.h
  * source/vm/hvm.c
  * source/compiler/genc.c
  * source/compiler/hbfix.c
  * source/compiler/hbpcode.c
  * source/compiler/harbour.c
    + Added support for new HB_P_PUSHGLOBAL and HB_P_POPGLOBAL.

  * source/compiler/harbour.slx
  * source/compiler/harbour.sly
    + Added support for new syntax:
      GLOBAL <Var> [ := <exp> ] [,...]
      GLOBAL <Array> \[ <length>\] [,...]
      GLOBAL EXTERNAL <Var> [,...]

  * include/hberrors.h
  * source/compiler/hbgenerr.c
    + Added new error messages:
        "Misplaced Global declaration \'%s\'.",
        "Too many Global declarations \'%s\'.",
        "External Global declaration can not include initializer \'%s\'."

  * source/vm/garbage.c
    + Added hb_vm_pGlobals to sweep.

  /*
     NEW Global Variables are much like STATICs only much FASTER. The added benefit, is that GLOBAL variables
     can be shared between different modules like PUBLIC variables, but with the speed and efficency of declared
     variables. For example, file1.prg may declare:

        GLOBAL MyGlobal

     and File2.prg might gain access, by declaring:

        GLOBAL EXTERNAL MyGlobal

     both files may now utilize MyGlobal throught all of the functions of both files.
   */

  + tests/global1.prg
  + tests/global2.prg
    + New demo files for the new GLOBAL and GLOBAL EXTERNAL syntax and usage.

  * bin/bld.bat
    * Modified to support build of 2 files.

    /* Please note -P -W are always included, so that extra parameter can be a prg name instead of compiler switch!!! */

  * tests/pp.prg
    * Fixed CompileRule to support same marker used more than once in match rule.

